<p>Ofcom complaints have soared to 21,673 following the performance, which featured a portrayal of a policeman kneeling on Ashley's neck. </p>

<p>On the show, presenter Piers, 55, reiterated his support for the routine saying: 'If you can't handle that without feeling the need to never watch BGT again or to complain to Ofcom, there's something wrong with you. </p>

<p>'You, you're the problem! You're part of the problem.</p>

<p>'By the way, if you don't like me saying this, then don't watch us either. Don't watch Good Morning Britain. Because I agree with Ashley Banjo and Diversity. And if you can't handle it Britain, wake up.' </p>

